util.lambda

Interface SupplierE<T>

  • All Superinterfaces:
    java.util.function.Supplier<T>
    Functional Interface:
    This is a functional interface and can therefore be used as the assignment target for a lambda expression or method reference.

    @FunctionalInterface
public interface SupplierE<T>
extends java.util.function.Supplier<T>
    Same as Supplier but can throw a checked exception. This way you can use a supplier that throws as an argument to methods that would not type-check with an exception-throwing lambda argument. Any thrown exception bubbles up as is without any wrapping as we use throwAsIfUnchecked to fool compiler and JVM.
    See Also:
    this..., ...and that.
